{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyMt9uPRwybtwIgc5kqpLO6I"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# 2342. Max Sum of a Pair With Equal Sum of Digits\n","\n","https://leetcode.com/problems/max-sum-of-a-pair-with-equal-sum-of-digits/description/\n","\n","You are given a **0-indexed** array `nums` consisting of positive integers. You can choose two indices `i` and `j`, such that `i != j`, and the sum of digits of the number `nums[i]` is equal to that of `nums[j]`.\n","\n","Return the maximum value of `nums[i] + nums[j]` that you can obtain over all possible indices `i` and `j` that satisfy the conditions.\n","\n","**Constraints:**\n","- `1 <= nums.length <= 10`<sup>`5`</sup>\n","- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10`<sup>`9`</sup>"],"metadata":{"id":"OhbFjTlo_zih"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Example 1:**\n","\n","- Input: `nums = [18,43,36,13,7]`\n","- Output: `54`\n","- Explanation: The pairs `(i, j)` that satisfy the conditions are:\n","\n"," - (0, 2), both numbers have a sum of digits equal to 9, and their sum is 18 + 36 = 54.\n","\n"," - (1, 4), both numbers have a sum of digits equal to 7, and their sum is 43 + 7 = 50.\n","\n","   So the maximum sum that we can obtain is 54.\n","\n","**Example 2:**\n","\n","- Input: `nums = [10,12,19,14]`\n","- Output: `-1`\n","- Explanation: There are no two numbers that satisfy the conditions, so we return -1."],"metadata":{"id":"IEpVafbfC7W-"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Observations\n","\n","- One pass through `nums` and find sum of each of its elements. Store the information in a dictionary with `key` is the sum value and `value` is list of `nums[i]` that has sum of it digits equals to key\n","- Loop over dictionary's values, sort and find `ans = values[-1] + values[-2]`\n","- Return the maxium value of `ans`."],"metadata":{"id":"e4M1bpIEDWc6"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["test_cases = [\n","    {\n","        \"input\": {\n","            \"nums\": [18,43,36,13,7],\n","        },\n","        \"output\": 54\n","    },\n","    {\n","        \"input\": {\n","            \"nums\": [10,12,19,14],\n","        },\n","        \"output\": -1\n","    },\n","]"],"metadata":{"id":"wNzMYBytDXO7","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1739372561971,"user_tz":-420,"elapsed":351,"user":{"displayName":"Duy Võ Minh","userId":"02029714770423543928"}}},"execution_count":1,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from typing import List\n","from collections import defaultdict\n","from collections import deque\n","\n","class Solution:\n","    def maximumSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n","        sum_nums = defaultdict(list)\n","\n","        for num in nums:\n","            sum_of_digits = self.calculateSumDigit(num)\n","            sum_nums[sum_of_digits].append(num)\n","\n","        ans = -1\n","        for values in sum_nums.values():\n","            if len(values) >= 2:\n","                values.sort()\n","                ans = max(ans, values[-1] + values[-2])\n","\n","        return ans\n","\n","    def calculateSumDigit(self, num: int) -> int:\n","        sum = 0\n","        while num > 0:\n","            sum += num % 10\n","            num //= 10\n","        return sum"],"metadata":{"id":"7N6VBRdIDUwD","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1739374645205,"user_tz":-420,"elapsed":623,"user":{"displayName":"Duy Võ Minh","userId":"02029714770423543928"}}},"execution_count":8,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["solution = Solution()\n","for test_case in test_cases:\n","    result = solution.maximumSum(test_case[\"input\"][\"nums\"])\n","    if result != test_case[\"output\"]:\n","        print(f'Failed test case with input: {test_case[\"input\"]} and output: {test_case[\"output\"]} vs result: {result}')"],"metadata":{"id":"CMDKnxwjGL6v","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1739374645205,"user_tz":-420,"elapsed":3,"user":{"displayName":"Duy Võ Minh","userId":"02029714770423543928"}}},"execution_count":9,"outputs":[]}]}